The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence and other officials during a visit to Pecan Ridge Plantation in Bainbridge, Georgia, following the devastation caused by Hurricane Michael. The officials expressed their support for the farmers and communities affected by the storm and assured them that they would receive assistance. They discussed the impact on agriculture, particularly the loss of pecan trees, and the need for long-term recovery efforts. The Vice President also addressed the issue of the federal deficit and the importance of a growing economy in addressing it. The officials also briefly mentioned the investigation into the disappearance of journalist Jamal Khashoggi and the upcoming visit of Secretary of Treasury Steven Mnuchin to Saudi Arabia.